Key Match Events: Antetokounmpo recorded a double-double with 31 points and 16 rebounds.
Lillard scored 34 points to lead the Bucks.
Milwaukee went on a 17-1 run late in the third quarter, sparked by Lillard and Antetokounmpo.
Pre-Game Insights: Giannis Antetokounmpo returned from a right adductor strain after missing a game.
Post-Match Reflections: The Bucks snapped a six-game losing streak.
Milwaukee avoided their first seven-game skid since March 2014.
